EXTENDED OUTLOOK
WEDNESDAY TO SATURDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE MARITIME AND COASTGUARD AGENCY
AT 242300 UTC
ON WEDNESDAY EVENING A LARGE ATLANTIC ANTI-CYCLONE 1039 EXTENDS EWARDS
ACROSS THE UK. MEANWHILE THE SEASONAL LOW IS SLOW MOV OVER IBERIA AND AN
AREA OF LOW PRESSURE IN THE BALTIC SEA SLWY MOVS EWARDS AND FILLS. BY MIDDAY
THURSDAY AN AREA OF LOW PRESSURE WILL DEVELOP JUST W OF FITZROY 1013 THIS
WILL BECOME SLOW MOV AND DEEPEN A LITTLE DURING FRIDAY AS THE ATLANTIC RIDGE
DECLINES. A FURTHER ANTICYCLONE 1029 WILL DEVELOP OVER THE N SEA WHERE
IT WILL REMAIN SLOW MOV THROUGH SATURDAY. STRG WINDS WILL AFFECT THE EERN
N SEA ON WEDNESDAY NIGHT PERHAPS REACHING NEAR GALE STRENGTH IN SEA AREA
FISHER WITH STRG NE WINDS ALSO EXP THROUGH THE ENGLISH CHANNEL.
THESE STRG WINDS WILL PERSIST THROUGH THURSDAY BUT SLWY EASE LATER ON FRIDAY
AND OVERNIGHT INTO SATURDAY. NO HAZARDOUS WINDS ARE EXP ELSEWHERE IN CULLERCOATS.
